  "text": "IRD (%) ICVL-4 (%) ST-GCN [CITATION_1] In the ablation study, we first investigate the role of the proposed strategy of selecting informative frames for skeleton-based action recognition. Second, we examine the strategy for how to connect the object to the human body in OHA-GCN in formulating object-related pose graphs. Finally, we verify the effectiveness of the object-related human pose in recognizing object-related actions. We will show improvement using the proposed components in our framework compared with the state-of-the-art method, ST-GCN [CITATION_2] , for skeleton-based action recognition.",
